Class CubicBezier

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode, SBase, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport

    public class CubicBezier
extends LineSegment
    Represents smooth curves in the Layout package.

    It represents a Bezier curve, and is readily available in most graphics APIs. The class CubicBezier is derived from LineSegment. It consists of four elements: the two inherited elements 'start' and 'end', which specify the starting point and the endpoint of the cubic bezier curve, and two elements 'basePoint1' and 'basePoint2', which specify the two additional base points that are needed to describe a cubic bezier curve. These basepoints also allow tools that cannot render bezier curves to approximate them by directly connecting the four points.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Nicolas Rodriguez, Andreas Dräger, David Vetter
